translated: Högsrum, Kalmar County, son of a public school teacher, Axel H. larsson and Alma Larsson. Married in 1933 to Gertrud Stadigh and had a son named Klas born in 1941. He passed his high school exams in Kalmar in 1918, land surveying exams in 1923, and in 1926, he passed his exams in agricultural engineering. He studied photogrammetry at the University of Jena in 1931, going on study trips to Switzerland in 1930, Austria and Hungary in 1932, and Great Britain in 1934. He worked as a department head in land surveying from 1928 to 1931 and as an assistant in land surveying education from 1929 to 1931. He initiated and managed land surveying districts in Kinna between 1931 and 1938 before becoming a district land surveyor in Linköping from 1938 and onwards. Between 1941 and 1944, he was a board member of the Swedish Society for Photogrammetry, and he authored various articles in professional journals specialized in geodesy and photogrammetry.
